The paper discusses the integration of scientific knowledge with data science models to enable scientific discovery, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions specific applications in materials discovery (cs.CE), climate science (cs.SI), and hydrology, which are all sub-disciplines of computer science. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning models (cs.DL) in theory-guided data science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.CE, cs.SI, and cs.DL.
